1
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,980
=Wonder Wall=

2
00:01:35,010 --> 00:01:37,880
=Episode 9=

3
00:01:56,359 --> 00:01:57,079
Shiqi!

4
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:00,400
Open the door!

5
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:02,560
It's Ouyang Qing.

6
00:02:03,439 --> 00:02:06,079
I can see the light flickering.

7
00:02:06,959 --> 00:02:08,000
Stop hiding.

8
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:11,439
I already saw you!

9
00:02:11,919 --> 00:02:13,240
I'll tell my dad

10
00:02:13,639 --> 00:02:15,400
that you're ignoring me.

11
00:02:15,479 --> 00:02:16,840
Ouyang Shiqi!

12
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:19,319
Stop yelling in the dead of night.

13
00:02:19,639 --> 00:02:20,360
We're trying to sleep.

14
00:02:20,879 --> 00:02:22,080
I got dumped.

15
00:02:22,479 --> 00:02:24,039
Do you have any sympathy?

16
00:02:24,199 --> 00:02:24,919
I'll call the police!

17
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:26,000
Just you wait!

18
00:02:29,479 --> 00:02:30,840
Ouyang Shiqi,

19
00:02:31,879 --> 00:02:33,199
he said I was not good-looking.

20
00:02:33,719 --> 00:02:34,960
He dumped me.

21
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:37,120
But I spent a whole year in England

22
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:38,879
eating nothing but fish and chips

23
00:02:38,879 --> 00:02:40,840
just to be with him.

24
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:43,199
Ouyang Shiqi!

25
00:02:44,719 --> 00:02:46,080
Officer,

26
00:02:47,479 --> 00:02:49,639
I got my heart broken.

27
00:03:24,759 --> 00:03:25,479
Man the decks.

28
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:35,520
Isn't it loud?

29
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:36,520
Should I take you home first?

30
00:03:41,439 --> 00:03:42,080
You want a drink?

31
00:03:42,479 --> 00:03:43,599
Who's the lightweight here?

32
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:44,360
Get drunk?

33
00:03:53,159 --> 00:03:54,120
Why turn off the light

34
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,039
every time I knock?

35
00:03:56,039 --> 00:03:56,919
This door

36
00:03:57,159 --> 00:03:58,039
has a glass window.

37
00:03:58,039 --> 00:03:59,199
I can see right in.

38
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:08,280
What's wrong?

39
00:04:09,879 --> 00:04:10,520
Not feeling well?

40
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,400
Since you're free, let's talk.

41
00:04:15,479 --> 00:04:16,519
Your mom told me

42
00:04:16,759 --> 00:04:18,079
you drew monsters on those red socks

43
00:04:18,079 --> 00:04:20,079
and gave them to your classmates.

44
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:24,439
Who's this supposed to be?

45
00:04:25,399 --> 00:04:26,240
Wu Xiaoxuan's dad.

46
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:29,959
You captured his look perfectly.

47
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,720
Looks like a troll.

48
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,240
Who is this?

49
00:04:37,839 --> 00:04:38,399
It's you.

50
00:04:38,959 --> 00:04:39,839
Is that really

51
00:04:39,839 --> 00:04:41,879
how I look in your eyes?

52
00:04:43,879 --> 00:04:45,680
Ever since they said
you won the lottery,

53
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:46,680
you've changed.

54
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:49,279
Your eyes were never big,

55
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:50,680
but they used to have me in them.

56
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:51,959
And mom.

57
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,920
and my two grandmas.

58
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:54,680
And light.

59
00:04:55,439 --> 00:04:56,319
But now,

60
00:04:56,879 --> 00:04:57,959
you're just stuffed

61
00:04:57,959 --> 00:04:58,680
with junk.

62
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:04,480
Is there light in my eyes now?

63
00:05:07,879 --> 00:05:08,800
Do you know why

64
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:09,879
I gave my classmates socks?

65
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:11,360
Sharing. You're rich now.

66
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:14,319
There's no light.

67
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:29,319
Once

68
00:05:30,439 --> 00:05:31,600
in my dream,

69
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:34,480
someone handed me a note

70
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:36,800
with a string of numbers on it.

71
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:39,879
They told me
it was Chen Liyang's number.

72
00:05:40,959 --> 00:05:42,439
But two of the digits were smudged.

73
00:05:43,199 --> 00:05:43,879
I couldn't make them out.

74
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:46,639
So I tried every combination.

75
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:48,720
I made 12 calls.

76
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:51,720
34 calls.

77
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:53,560
None was right.

78
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:55,360
No one answered.

79
00:05:56,319 --> 00:05:58,000
Just as I was about
to make another call,

80
00:05:59,279 --> 00:06:00,199
I woke up

81
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,839
and someone came in.

82
00:06:04,439 --> 00:06:04,959
Who?

83
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:08,079
The police.

84
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,519
The police came.

85
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:13,759
Almost.

86
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,519
I almost succeeded.

87
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,000
What a shame.

88
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:47,759
(2018)
Happy birthday!

89
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:51,759
It's good.

90
00:07:29,519 --> 00:07:29,959
No.

91
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:31,160
That's not the taste.

92
00:07:32,959 --> 00:07:33,839
Not this.

93
00:07:41,319 --> 00:07:42,720
Why is it wrong?

94
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,079
Why can't I make

95
00:07:47,079 --> 00:07:48,199
the flavor right?

96
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:51,439
You eat longevity noodles

97
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,639
and you're supposed to live long.

98
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:09,560
Give the money back to them.

99
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,160
That money killed my father.

100
00:08:14,399 --> 00:08:15,959
I don't want to see it again.

101
00:08:37,799 --> 00:08:38,799
You shouldn't let her drink.

102
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:42,279
Who are you?

103
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:48,840
When she drinks,

104
00:08:49,639 --> 00:08:50,480
it brings back a lot

105
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:51,360
of bad memories.

106
00:08:52,399 --> 00:08:53,240
She'd be upset.

107
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:56,960
Take good care of her.

108
00:08:58,080 --> 00:08:58,759
Don't cross the line.

109
00:09:43,039 --> 00:09:44,000
I can't do it anymore.

110
00:09:46,279 --> 00:09:47,159
Let me sit for a while.

111
00:09:50,639 --> 00:09:51,480
I need a minute.

112
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:12,519
We built the houses above us

113
00:10:13,639 --> 00:10:15,159
with our own hands.

114
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,240
Every angle is beautiful.

115
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:22,879
We built that house,

116
00:10:23,679 --> 00:10:25,320
but we can't afford it.

117
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:27,600
A house that nice...

118
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:29,799
we can only look at it.

119
00:10:30,159 --> 00:10:31,159
What can you do?

120
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:32,840
We don't have the money.

121
00:10:36,639 --> 00:10:37,279
Money

122
00:10:38,759 --> 00:10:39,879
is a wonderful thing.

123
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,840
We work so hard.

124
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:44,919
Why doesn't it ever come to us?

125
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:48,720
Isn't it right there?

126
00:10:50,039 --> 00:10:51,159
Break through and we'll have it.

127
00:10:52,879 --> 00:10:53,679
I can't dig anymore.

128
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:55,960
I'm starving.

129
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,679
Didn't you have dinner?

130
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:02,120
Just steamed buns with some pickles.

131
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:03,960
That's not very filling.

132
00:11:06,679 --> 00:11:07,080
How about

133
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:10,320
we get something nice to eat?

134
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,240
What you left

135
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:33,000
has been found.

136
00:11:35,759 --> 00:11:37,120
I know what to do.

137
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:41,120
As long as it belongs to Zinuo,

138
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,240
no one can take it from her.

139
00:11:46,620 --> 00:11:50,010
(2011)

140
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:55,159
Zinuo feels insecure.

141
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:57,159
She's like a snail.

142
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:58,519
She needs

143
00:11:58,519 --> 00:11:59,960
a shell to protect herself.

144
00:12:01,399 --> 00:12:03,080
She has to carry it everywhere she goes.

145
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:05,480
It's exhausting for her.

146
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:08,120
Ms. Li is too strict with her.

147
00:12:08,759 --> 00:12:09,840
She feels awful.

148
00:12:12,799 --> 00:12:14,159
I'm the buffer

149
00:12:15,159 --> 00:12:16,759
between her and her mom.

150
00:12:17,879 --> 00:12:18,600
You're the same.

151
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:21,639
One day, if her mom

152
00:12:21,639 --> 00:12:22,960
takes away her shell,

153
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,440
you should be her shell.

154
00:12:26,679 --> 00:12:27,399
Don't worry.

155
00:12:28,519 --> 00:12:29,480
I'll do

156
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:30,879
what I should do well.

157
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:03,120
Damei.

158
00:13:03,759 --> 00:13:04,639
Damei.

159
00:13:17,490 --> 00:13:19,250
(Du Lei)

160
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:23,559
Hello.

161
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:26,679
The best way to honor someone who's gone

162
00:13:27,639 --> 00:13:29,480
is to do what they

163
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:31,000
wanted you to do.

164
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:32,639
He left thirty million.

165
00:13:33,159 --> 00:13:34,279
You take thirty million.

166
00:13:34,759 --> 00:13:35,919
If he thought it was yours,

167
00:13:36,519 --> 00:13:37,600
then it's yours.

168
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:00,159
Hello.

169
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:01,679
Hello.

170
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,240
I've told you so many times.

171
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:05,679
Don't drink straight from the bottle.

172
00:14:05,679 --> 00:14:06,440
It's unsanitary.

173
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:07,519
Pour it into a cup.

174
00:14:07,559 --> 00:14:08,200
You don't even care

175
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:09,480
about how I'm feeling.

176
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:10,960
No, you just worry about the hygiene.

177
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:11,639
So heartless.

178
00:14:11,639 --> 00:14:12,120
How could

179
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:12,960
others drink from it?

180
00:14:14,519 --> 00:14:15,399
Sorry about that, sis.

181
00:14:15,399 --> 00:14:16,559
Don't call her that.

182
00:14:17,799 --> 00:14:19,200
She's my cousin, Ouyang Qing.

183
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:19,879
Yeah.

184
00:14:20,279 --> 00:14:21,080
We're cousins.

185
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:22,039
Hello, Qing.

186
00:14:22,679 --> 00:14:24,159
We were born into the same basin.

187
00:14:24,279 --> 00:14:25,440
He's only three hours older than me,

188
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:26,559
but he's always bossing me around.

189
00:14:26,559 --> 00:14:28,080
you help me keep him down from now on.

190
00:14:28,440 --> 00:14:29,399
We're on the same side.

191
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:29,960
Take him down.

192
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:39,600
All wild

193
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:41,320
and flashy.

194
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:43,000
How can I go out wearing this?

195
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:44,679
It's so ugly.

196
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:50,519
And the color is red.

197
00:14:51,159 --> 00:14:52,320
Like a red lantern.

198
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:57,480
6,999 yuan?

199
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:59,039
Oh, my god!

200
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:08,320
It's from my daughter.

201
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:09,960
Good-looking.

202
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:13,080
After tailing her for a few days,

203
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:13,759
I found

204
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:16,159
Wen Yitong's mom is very frugal.

205
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:18,320
She won't spend a penny
on anything unnecessary.

206
00:15:18,919 --> 00:15:19,480
Now she

207
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:21,240
is in charge
of the family's groceries.

208
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:22,919
Every two days,

209
00:15:22,919 --> 00:15:24,120
she will go to the wet market.

210
00:15:24,919 --> 00:15:26,039
So going by this pattern,

211
00:15:26,519 --> 00:15:27,200
tomorrow

212
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:28,879
(Grandma, don't forget fried chicken!)
is her market day.

213
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:30,519
She's a pretty girl,

214
00:15:30,519 --> 00:15:33,200
but her handwriting is a mess.

215
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,720
Every time she goes to the wet market,

216
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:37,080
(Wet Market)
she'll first go to this place

217
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,399
to buy some vegetables first.

218
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:41,960
Then she takes a detour to here

219
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,279
and buy some meat.

220
00:15:43,759 --> 00:15:44,639
There's a discount today,

221
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:47,000
Cut a piece from here.

222
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:47,759
Right about here.

223
00:15:48,279 --> 00:15:49,120
Finally,

224
00:15:49,279 --> 00:15:50,960
she'll go to the seafood section.

225
00:15:51,480 --> 00:15:52,039
Got it.

226
00:15:52,039 --> 00:15:53,559
So we strike
at the seafood section, right?

227
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:54,320
It's slippery there.

228
00:15:54,480 --> 00:15:55,240
That won't work.

229
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:57,440
It's slippery, sure,
but it's also crowded.

230
00:15:57,440 --> 00:15:58,720
Other people may disrupt our plan.

231
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:00,159
So what do we do?

232
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:01,279
One portion of popcorn chicken.

233
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:02,320
Large. Make it large.

234
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:03,039
Look.

235
00:16:03,559 --> 00:16:05,360
When she comes out of the market,

236
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:07,080
we set up a roadblock

237
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:08,159
right here.

238
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:11,200
Always fixing the roads.

239
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:13,200
Roadwork during the day

240
00:16:13,559 --> 00:16:14,679
is a huge hassle.

241
00:16:14,879 --> 00:16:16,200
They weren't doing it just now.

242
00:16:17,279 --> 00:16:17,879
She

243
00:16:18,399 --> 00:16:19,320
must take

244
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:21,000
those stairs in that lane.

245
00:16:21,519 --> 00:16:23,120
We'll pour the oil right there,

246
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:23,679
on those steps.

247
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:27,519
Those stairs have no handrails.

248
00:16:28,159 --> 00:16:28,679
A slip.

249
00:16:28,919 --> 00:16:30,039
She'll fall straight down.

250
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:42,279
Which scoundrel

251
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:45,000
has poured oil on the road?

252
00:16:45,399 --> 00:16:45,960
After that,

253
00:16:46,120 --> 00:16:47,879
I'd wait for her nearby.

254
00:16:54,919 --> 00:16:55,879
What's the matter?

255
00:16:56,039 --> 00:16:57,200
Why are you on the ground?

256
00:16:58,039 --> 00:16:59,200
I fell.

257
00:16:59,879 --> 00:17:00,759
Please help me up.

258
00:17:00,759 --> 00:17:01,159
Okay.

259
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:04,200
Sorry about it,

260
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:06,519
but can you try to get up by yourself?

261
00:17:06,519 --> 00:17:07,599
I can't move.

262
00:17:09,559 --> 00:17:10,759
Who poured oil on the road?

263
00:17:10,759 --> 00:17:12,759
Be careful, it's very slippery.

264
00:17:13,359 --> 00:17:16,119
I'm currently in the alley
on Simingquan Road.

265
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:18,720
I just passed by this lane

266
00:17:19,039 --> 00:17:20,319
when I saw this lady fall.

267
00:17:20,319 --> 00:17:20,799
Now it's

268
00:17:20,799 --> 00:17:21,960
1:32 p.m.

269
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:23,720
Madam,

270
00:17:24,079 --> 00:17:24,680
can you try

271
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:25,720
to turn your head

272
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:26,319
to one side?

273
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:27,279
My head?

274
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:29,039
I can't move.

275
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:30,519
I can't move.

276
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:31,200
No good.

277
00:17:31,319 --> 00:17:32,839
She's so painful
that she can't turn her head.

278
00:17:32,839 --> 00:17:34,039
I'm calling an ambulance now.

279
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:34,839
I...

280
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:36,720
Madam,

281
00:17:36,920 --> 00:17:38,960
I'm a migrant worker
from the countryside.

282
00:17:39,359 --> 00:17:40,119
I'm poor.

283
00:17:40,240 --> 00:17:42,119
Everything I earn
goes back to support my family.

284
00:17:42,480 --> 00:17:43,599
Don't try to scam me.

285
00:17:43,759 --> 00:17:45,160
No, I fell myself.

286
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:47,480
I'm not going to scam you.

287
00:17:47,599 --> 00:17:48,880
Okay, these are the words I want.

288
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:50,559
I've recorded it as evidence.

289
00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:52,359
Call my daughter.

290
00:17:52,519 --> 00:17:53,200
Okay.

291
00:17:53,839 --> 00:17:54,519
Don't panic.

292
00:17:56,960 --> 00:17:57,839
Ouyang finally agreed

293
00:17:57,839 --> 00:17:58,960
to return the money to us.

294
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:00,640
I really want

295
00:18:00,640 --> 00:18:01,640
