370
00:20:40,799 --> 00:20:41,599
Just for peace of mind.

371
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:43,799
Alright.

372
00:20:50,359 --> 00:20:51,599
I brought over a bowl of noodles.

373
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:52,799
I asked, "Hot or not?"

374
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:54,119
He at once got mad and said,

375
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:55,200
"I came to eat here.

376
00:20:55,359 --> 00:20:56,359
Why are you kicking me out?"

377
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:58,200
I dared not say that again.

378
00:20:58,200 --> 00:21:00,920
I'd just ask whether it's too hot.

379
00:21:02,839 --> 00:21:03,519
That's hilarious.

380
00:21:18,720 --> 00:21:19,400
I'm done.

381
00:21:21,599 --> 00:21:22,279
It's good.

382
00:21:22,640 --> 00:21:23,359
Did you make it?

383
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:26,559
My husband is a cook.

384
00:21:26,839 --> 00:21:28,359
My mom is a dish washer.

385
00:21:28,559 --> 00:21:29,400
As for me,

386
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:31,000
I cook and wash dishes.

387
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:32,799
I worked as a housekeeper

388
00:21:32,799 --> 00:21:33,720
and a caregiver for ten years.

389
00:21:33,799 --> 00:21:35,720
I used the money I made
to open a restaurant.

390
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:37,119
Those who came for noodles

391
00:21:37,160 --> 00:21:38,279
were all regulars.

392
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:39,880
The landlord saw I was making money

393
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:40,920
and wanted to

394
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:42,000
